1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the statistics of effective fading gain, which is a concept related to information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the impact of cell selection on the effective fading distribution in a multi-tier cellular network, which is a networking and internet architecture problem. 
3. cs.COMM (Communication and Networking) - The paper deals with the communication aspect of cellular networks and how cell selection affects the channel fading gain. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper analyzes the system of a multi-tier cellular network and how it can be controlled through cell selection. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper may be relevant to multimedia applications that rely on cellular networks, as the effective fading gain affects the quality of the received signal.
